[4] Selected media reports of transmission outside mainland China
A. Japanese cruise ship
Date: Sun 9 Feb 2020
Source: ABS CBN news / Kyodo News [edited]
https://news.abs-cbn.com/overseas/02/10/20/4-filipinos-among-6-new-coronavirus-infections-on-cruise-ship-in-japan


4 Filipinos, among 6 new coronavirus infections on cruise ship in Japan
----------------------------------
Six more people on a cruise ship quarantined in Yokohama have tested positive for a new coronavirus, the health ministry said Sunday [9 Feb 2020], bringing the total number of those infected on board to 70.

The 5 crew members and 1 passenger -- 4 Filipinos, 1 American, and 1 Ukrainian in their 20s to 70s -- have no serious symptoms, the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare said. The ministry said it has tested 336 potentially infected people from around 3700 passengers and crew on the vessel, and the latest results on 57 people turned up the 6 new cases.

The ship, carrying customers from more than 50 countries and regions, has been kept in quarantine since Monday [4 Feb 2020] after a passenger, who disembarked in Hong Kong, was found to be infected with the pneumonia-causing virus.

The government is also working on a request to get medication to those on board who are suffering from chronic conditions, health minister Katsunobu Kato said on a TV program the same day.

The overall number of infected in Japan now stands at 96, including 10 people who evacuated from the Chinese city of Wuhan, at the center of the outbreak, on government-chartered flights. Another 16 includes tourists and a tour bus driver. A Japanese national, suspected of being infected with the coronavirus, died Saturday [8 Feb 2020] in Wuhan. The man in his 60s would be the 1st Japanese death resulting from the virus if confirmed.

In mainland China, the death toll reached 811, the country's National Health Commission said Sunday [9 Feb 2020], more than the SARS global death toll of 774. The cases of confirmed infections have risen to more than 37 000 nationwide.

--
